author: julianfoad
msg: Tidy the symmetric merge code by making the svn_client__symmetric_merge_t
structure opaque and providing an accessor function for the one access that
is currently needed. The main pragmatic reason to make it opaque right now
is that we want to make the symmetric merge client APIs fully public, but
the svn_client__pathrev_t type used in this struct is module-private.
(svn_client__symmetric_merge_t): Make this opaque, moving the definition
(symmetric_merge): Use the new accessor function instead of direct access.
